1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commemorate the one hundredth anniversary of the Louisiana Municipal Association.
3 WHEREAS, on January 28, 1926, mayors from cities, towns, and villages across
4 Louisiana convened in Alexandria as the Louisiana Conference of Mayors to establish a
5 unified voice for local government; this organization became the Louisiana Municipal
6 Association (LMA); and
7 WHEREAS, the LMA was founded to foster cooperation and success among
8 municipalities and to provide a forum for addressing matters of mutual concern affecting
9 local government throughout the state; and
10 WHEREAS, for the past one hundred years, LMA municipalities have demonstrated
11 dedication, integrity, and innovation in public service while promoting economic growth,
12 civic engagement, infrastructure development, and quality of life for Louisiana communities;
13 and
14 WHEREAS, the mission of the LMA is anchored in four pillars: education, service,
15 training, and advocacy for its member mayors, related organizations, and affiliates; its
16 mission serves to strengthen the effectiveness of municipal leadership statewide; and
17 WHEREAS, the LMA provides professional guidance, local government advocacy
18 at the legislature, support from legislators across the state, and collaborative problem-solving
19 with key local government partners to champion municipalities and respond to changing
20 economic, environmental, infrastructure, and public service needs; and
